%N A397778 Lengths of longest legs of Pythagorean triangles corresponding to a record number of such triangles.
%C A397778 Indices of record values in A056137.
%e A397778 For a right triangle with longest leg of 60, the lengths other sides are: 11,25,32,45. The corresponding hypotenuses are: 61,65,68,75. All triangles with a longest leg of less than 60 have 3 or fewer triangles.
%o A397778 (PARI) \\ b(n) is A056137(n)
%o A397778 b(n) = my(r=n^2); sumdiv(r, d, my(t=r/d-d); t>0 && t%2 == 0 && t^2<4*r)
%o A397778 upto(lim) = { my(m=0,L=List()); for(i=1, lim, if(numdiv(i^2)>2*m, my(t=b(i));if(t>m,m=t; listput(L,i)))); Vec(L) } \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 10 2026
%Y A397778 Cf. A056137.
